note right of prospecting_configurations
Hourly prospecting automation persists both the enforced
runtime snapshot cadence and next_run_at on the same schedule
so the scheduler and operator UI do not drift apart.
Stale RUNNING rows are also recoverable once the due slot elapses,
preventing interrupted cycles from wedging the hourly loop.
end note

note right of proto_idea_sources
Each row is the Proto-Idea stage's claimed view of one upstream
source artefact. The source payload stays intact for traceability,
while processing status, attempts, errors, parsed output, and
deduplication notes make retries and inspection straightforward.
The applied extraction policy is stored both by foreign key and
by policy snapshot so each run remains reproducible even if the
administrator later changes the live policy.
end note

note right of proto_ideas
One source can yield zero, one, or many proto-ideas.
Each stored proto-idea preserves explicit source signals separately
from inferred signals so downstream refinement can stay grounded.
end note

note right of proto_idea_extraction_policies
Stores the administrator-defined policy that shapes Proto-Idea Agent
behavior at runtime. The policy remains structured and bounded rather
than acting as a free-form prompt editor, and the latest run metadata
supports simple operational visibility from the admin UI.
end note

